The rogues are here.

Today was pub day.&nbsp; ROGUES, the latest gigantic crossgenre anthology from Gardner Dozois and yours truly, is now available at your favorite local bookstore on on-line bookseller.

<a href="http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/207467/207467_original.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="Rogues comp A March 17 lo res" src="http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/207467/207467_600.jpg" title="Rogues comp A March 17 lo res" /></a>

If you enjoyed WARRIORS and DANGEROUS WOMEN, we think you&#39;ll love ROGUES.&nbsp; It may be our strongest anthology yet.&nbsp;&nbsp; We have some amazing writers and some incredible stories in this one.&nbsp; The table of contents:

George R.R. Martin &ldquo;Everybody Loves a Rogue&rdquo; (Introduction)
Joe Abercrombie &ldquo;Tough Times All Over&rdquo;
Gillian Flynn &ldquo;What Do You Do?&rdquo;
Matthew Hughes &ldquo;The Inn of the Seven Blessings&rdquo;
Joe R. Lansdale &ldquo;Bent Twig&rdquo;
Michael Swanwick &ldquo;Tawny Petticoats&rdquo;
David Ball &ldquo;Provenance&rdquo;
Carrie Vaughn &ldquo;The Roaring Twenties&rdquo;
Scott Lynch &ldquo;A Year and a Day in Old Theradane&rdquo;
Bradley Denton &ldquo;Bad Brass&rdquo;
Cherie Priest &ldquo;Heavy Metal&rdquo;
Daniel Abraham &ldquo;The Meaning of Love&rdquo;
Paul Cornell &ldquo;A Better Way to Die&rdquo;
Steven Saylor &ldquo;Ill Seen in Tyre&rdquo;
Garth Nix &ldquo;A Cargo of Ivories&rdquo;
Walter Jon Williams &ldquo;Diamonds From Tequila&rdquo;
Phyllis Eisenstein &ldquo;The Caravan to Nowhere&rdquo;
Lisa Tuttle &ldquo;The Curious Affair of the Dead Wives&rdquo;
Neil Gaiman &ldquo;How the Marquis Got His Coat Back&rdquo;
Connie Willis &ldquo;Now Showing&rdquo;
Patrick Rothfuss &ldquo;The Lightning Tree&rdquo;
George R.R. Martin &quot;The Rogue Prince, or, A King&#39;s Brother.&quot;

Enjoy the read!

(And yes, New Mexicans, we have copies for sale at the Jean Cocteau, and I will be there tomorrow evening to sign them.&nbsp; We&#39;re having a benefit for the New Mexico Book Association.&nbsp; Come join us, have a beer, buy a book, hear me read).
